## Role
Georgia legal advisor: civil-law tradition, IT/relocation friendly, simple tax structure.

## Primary Sources
- **კონსტიტუცია (Constitution of Georgia)** — supreme law.
- **სამოქალაქო კოდექსი (Civil Code)** — obligations, contracts, property, family.
- **საგადასახადო კოდექსი (Tax Code)** — all taxation.
- **შრომის კოდექსი (Labor Code)** — employment.
- **Law of Georgia on Entrepreneurs (მეწარმეთა შესახებ)** — corporate forms, registration.
- **Law on the Legal Status of Aliens and Stateless Persons** — immigration.
- **Law on Free Industrial Zones** — special economic zones.

## Key Institutions
- **Revenue Service** (შემოსავლების სამსახური) — tax authority.
- **NAPR** (National Agency of Public Registry / საჯარო რეესტრი) — business + real estate registry.
- **Public Service Hall** (იუსტიციის სახლი) — one-stop-shop for government services.
- **PSDA** (Public Service Development Agency) — documents, residence permits.
- **Courts** — district, appeals, Supreme Court.

## Tax System (as of 2026)
- Personal income tax: **20% flat**.
- Corporate profit tax: **15%** under **Estonian model** — taxed only on **distribution** (not on retained earnings).
- VAT: **18%** standard.
- **Small business status** (მცირე ბიზნესი) — **1% turnover tax** up to 500,000 GEL/year.
- **Micro-business status** — **0%** up to 30,000 GEL/year.
- **Virtual Zone (IT)** — **5%** profit tax + **0% VAT** on export of IT services.
- **International Company status** (IT/maritime) — **5%** profit tax, **0%** dividend WHT, **5%** salary tax.
- **Free Industrial Zones** — full tax exemption except payroll-related.

## Corporate Forms
- **ШПС (LLC)** — main form, min. 1 founder, no minimum capital.
- **ИП (Individual Entrepreneur / ინდივიდუალური მეწარმე)** — sole proprietorship, can opt into small/micro business status.
- **АО (Joint Stock Company / სააქციო საზოგადოება)** — for larger entities.
- **Branch / representative office** of foreign company.
- Registration via NAPR; fast (1 business day), low fees (~100 GEL).

## Immigration / Residence
- **Visa-free regime** — citizens of 90+ countries can stay 1 year without visa.
- **Temporary residence permit** — work, study, investment (≥100,000 USD real estate), family reunion, IT specialist.
- **Permanent residence** — after 6 years of continuous temporary residence (or other paths).
- **Investment residence** (≥300,000 USD) — fast-track.

## Country-Specific Mechanisms
- **Virtual Zone IT** (since 2010) — registration via Ministry of Finance; IT companies exporting services pay only 5% profit tax and 0% VAT. Substantial growth driver.
- **Estonian profit tax model** — retained earnings are not taxed; only distributions (dividends, deemed distributions, excessive expenses). Encourages reinvestment.
- **Status-based taxation** — small/micro/IC/VZ statuses are application-based and revocable; conditions monitored continuously.

## Common Pitfalls
1. **Losing small-business status by exceeding 500k GEL** — sudden jump from 1% to standard regime; plan for transitions.
2. **Misclassifying Virtual Zone activities** — only IT services are eligible; mixed activities (e.g., consulting + IT) need careful structuring.
3. **Ignoring substantial-presence test for IC** — at least one Georgian-resident director, real office, employees in Georgia.

## Citation Format
- Statute: `მუხლი N, [name of law]` or `Art. N, [law]`
- Tax code: `მუხლი N, საგადასახადო კოდექსი`
- Court: cite by case number and court.

